## TabBar Component

The `TabBar` component provides a user interface for managing a collection of tabs. It allows users to switch between active tabs, close individual tabs, and open new ones.

### Key Exports

*   `TabBar`: A React functional component that renders the tab bar UI.

### Props

*   `tabs` (`Tab[]`): An array of `Tab` objects, where each object represents a tab and must have at least an `id` and `label` property.
*   `activeTabId` (`string`): The ID of the currently active tab.
*   `onSwitch` (`(id: string) => void`): A callback function invoked when a user attempts to switch to a different tab. It receives the ID of the target tab.
*   `onClose` (`(id: string) => void`): A callback function invoked when a user attempts to close a tab. It receives the ID of the tab to be closed.
*   `onAdd` (`() => void`): A callback function invoked when the "New tab" button is clicked.

### Usage Example

```tsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { TabBar } from './TabBar'; // Assuming TabBar is in the same directory

interface Tab {
  id: string;
  label: string;
}

function App() {
  const [tabs, setTabs] = useState<Tab[]>([
    { id: 'tab1', label: 'Home' },
    { id: 'tab2', label: 'Settings' },
  ]);
  const [activeTabId, setActiveTabId] = useState<string>('tab1');
  const [nextTabId, setNextTabId] = useState(3);

  const handleSwitchTab = (id: string) => {
    setActiveTabId(id);
  };

  const handleCloseTab = (id: string) => {
    setTabs(tabs.filter(tab => tab.id !== id));
    if (activeTabId === id && tabs.length > 1) {
      setActiveTabId(tabs.find(tab => tab.id !== id)?.id || '');
    } else if (tabs.length === 1) {
      setActiveTabId('');
    }
  };

  const handleAddTab = () => {
    const newTabId = `tab${nextTabId}`;
    setTabs([...tabs, { id: newTabId, label: `New Tab ${nextTabId}` }]);
    setActiveTabId(newTabId);
    setNextTabId(prev => prev + 1);
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <TabBar
        tabs={tabs}
        activeTabId={activeTabId}
        onSwitch={handleSwitchTab}
        onClose={handleCloseTab}
        onAdd={handleAddTab}
      />
      {/* Render content for the active tab here */}
      <div>
        {activeTabId === 'tab1' && <div>Content for Home tab</div>}
        {activeTabId === 'tab2' && <div>Content for Settings tab</div>}
        {tabs.find(tab => tab.id === activeTabId)?.label && activeTabId.startsWith('tab') && activeTabId !== 'tab1' && activeTabId !== 'tab2' && <div>Content for {tabs.find(tab => tab.id === activeTabId)?.label} tab</div>}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```

### Notes

*   Tabs can be closed by clicking the '×' icon. 
*   Tabs can also be closed using the middle mouse button click (scroll wheel click) on the tab, provided there is more than one tab open.
*   The "New tab" button (`+`) is always visible and triggers the `onAdd` callback.
*   The close button (`×`) is only rendered if there is more than one tab.
*   The `title` attribute is set on each tab button for accessibility and hover information.
*   The `aria-label` attribute is used for the close button for better screen reader support.
